eNCA’s senior reporter Dasen Thathiah has the details. #eNCA #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A rural KZN community is demanding measures to keep animals inside the Hluhluwe-Imfolozi Park. Five elephants on the loose near Nqulwane village this weekend have been recaptured but it's not the first time animals have escaped from the park, and residents fear it will happen again. eNCA’s senior reporter Dasen Thathiah has the details.